Package: CEClust
Type: Package
Title: Composite Entropy Clustering (CEC) for Mixed Data
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      given = "Thierry",
      family = "Dumont",
      email = "tdumont@parisnanterre.fr",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Fits composite entropy clustering models for Gaussian,
    categorical, and mixed data. The package combines repeated-shot
    clustering at a fixed regularization value with linked-lambda diagnostic
    paths, bootstrap-based stability summaries, trajectory repair helpers,
    and visualization tools for interpreting how partitions evolve across the
    regularization grid. An optional compiled backend is used automatically
    when available.
